PresentationColumn.name: Postal Code
PresentationColumn.Description: The full Postcode for the Owning Party's primary address

PresentationColumn.name: Postal Area
PresentationColumn.Description: The first one or two letters of the postcode (anything before the first number). For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal Area is 'PL'

PresentationColumn.name: Postal District
PresentationColumn.Description: The first section of the postcode, before the last 3 characters. For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal District is PL14

PresentationColumn.name: Postal Sector
PresentationColumn.Description: The postcode minus the last two letters. For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal Sector is PL14 4

PresentationColumn.name: Solicitor Region
PresentationColumn.Description: The CRUK region which the postal district belongs to as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel e.g. PL14 is in Region 9

PresentationColumn.name: VF Regional Canvasser
PresentationColumn.Description: The Canvasser who is responsible for the area in which the owning party's primary address sits, as defined in the Postcode Admin table on Siebel
